20MiG%2021%20Bison%20jet%20was%20hit%20in%20a%20dogfight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%20had%20launched%20the%20retaliation%20for%20the%20Balakot%20airstrikes%20a%20day%20before.%20Varthaman%20was%20captured%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20Army%20and%20was%20released%20two%20days%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20willing%20to%20send%20an%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20aircraft%20to%20pick%20him%20up%20but%20Pakistan%20refused%20permission%3B%20the%20optics%20of%20an%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20plane%20landing%20in%20Islamabad%20after%20all%20that%20had%20happened%20over%20the%20previous%20three%20days%2C%20was%2C%20of%20course%2C%20not%20acceptable%20to%20Pakistan%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bisaria%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%2C%20'Anger%20Management%3A%20The%20Troubled%20Diplomatic%20Relationship%20Between%20India%20and%20Pakistan'%2C%20he%20also%20says%20several%20countries%20had%20offered%20to%20send%20special%20envoys%20over%20to%20the%20subcontinent%20but%20this%20was%20no%20longer%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20China%2C%20not%20to%20be%20left%20behind%2C%20had%20suggested%20that%20it%20could%20send%20its%20deputy%20minister%20to%20both%20countries%20to%20seek%20de-escalation.%20India%20had%20politely%20declined%20the%20offer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20book%20published%20by%20Rupa%2C%20Mr%20Bisaria%2C%20who%20had%20a%20distinguished%20diplomatic%20career%20spanning%2035%20years%2C%20delves%20into%20various%20aspects%20of%20India-Pakistan%20relations%20since%20Independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ties%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20came%20under%20severe%20strain%20after%20India's%20warplanes%20pounded%20a%20Jaish-e-Mohammed%20terrorist%20training%20camp%20in%20Balakot%20in%20Pakistan%20on%20February%2026%2C%202019%2C%20in%20response%20to%20the%20Pulwama%20terror%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bisaria%20says%20that%20the%20day%20after%20India's%20air%20strikes%20at%20Balakot%2C%20the%20ambassadors%20of%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20and%20France%20were%20informed%20during%20a%20briefing%20by%20the%20then%20Pakistan%20foreign%20secretary%20Tehmina%20Janjua%20about%20a%20message%20she%20received%20from%20the%20Pakistan%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bnine%20missiles%20from%20India%20had%20been%20pointed%20towards%20Pakistan%2C%20to%20be%20launched%20any%20time%20that%20day%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20foreign%20secretary%20requested%20the%20envoys%20to%20report%20this%20intelligence%20to%20their%20capitals%20and%20ask%20India%20not%20to%20escalate%20the%20situation.%20The%20diplomats%20promptly%20reported%20these%20developments%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20flurry%20of%20diplomatic%20activity%20in%20Islamabad%2C%20P5%20capitals%2C%20and%20in%20New%20Delhi%20that%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bisaria%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20permanent%20members%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%2C%20Russia%2C%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20China%20and%20France%20are%20known%20as%20P5%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20them%20recommended%20to%20her%20that%20Pakistan%20should%20convey%20its%20concerns%20directly%20to%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mr%20Bisaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bisaria%20also%20writes%20that%20then%20Pakistan%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%20wanted%20to%20talk%20to%20his%20Indian%20counterpart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20around%20midnight%20I%20got%20a%20call%20in%20Delhi%20from%20Pakistani%20High%20Commissioner%20Sohail%20Mahmood%2C%20now%20in%20Islamabad%2C%20who%20said%20that%20PM%20Imran%20Khan%20was%20keen%20to%20talk%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20checked%20upstairs%20and%20responded%20that%20our%20prime%20minister%20was%20not%20available%20at%20this%20hour%20but%20in%20case%20Imran%20Khan%20had%20any%20urgent%20message%20to%20convey%20he%20could%2C%20of%20course%2C%20convey%20it%20to%20me.%20I%20got%20no%20call%20back%20that%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20and%20UK%20envoys%20in%20Delhi%20got%20back%20overnight%20to%20India's%20foreign%20secretary%20to%20claim%20that%20Pakistan%20was%20now%20ready%20to%20de-escalate%20the%20situation%2C%20to%20act%20on%20India's%20dossier%2C%20and%20to%20seriously%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20terrorism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bisaria%20says%20%26quot%3BPakistan's%20PM%20would%20himself%20make%20these%20announcements%20and%20the%20pilot%20would%20be%20returned%20to%20India%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20India's%20%26quot%3Bcoercive%20diplomacy%26quot%3B%20had%20been%20effective%2C%20its%20expectations%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20of%20the%20world%20had%20been%20clear%2C%20backed%20by%20a%20credible%20resolve%20to%20escalate%20the%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrime%20Minister%20Modi%20would%20later%20say%20in%20a%20campaign%20speech%20that%2C%20'Fortunately%2C%20Pakistan%20announced%20that%20the%20pilot%20would%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20India.%20Else%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20%3Cem%3Eqatal%20ki%20raat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20night%20of%20bloodshed'%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20overall%20regional%20geopolitics%2C%20Mr%20Bisaria%20writes%20that%20Pakistan%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Imran%20Khan%20conveyed%20to%20China%20that%20it%20should%20support%20Islamabad%20since%20the%20United%20States%20decided%20to%20back%20India%20against%20China%2C%20but%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20%26quot%3Bdeclared%20that%20China%20would%20not%20be%20propping%20up%20Pakistan%20against%20India%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20also%20learnt%20that%20Khan%20had%20told%20the%20Chinese%20that%20they%20should%20support%20Pakistan%20since%20the%20US%20had%20decided%20to%20support%20India%20against%20China.%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20apparently%20responded%20sharply%20to%20Imran%20Khan%20for%20this%20simplistic%20geopolitical%20assessment%20and%20declared%20that%20China%20would%20not%20be%20propping%20up%20Pakistan%20against%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20had%20advised%20Khan%20that%20it%20was%20the%20US%20that%20could%20help%20Pakistan%20in%20its%20India%20relationship%20and%20it%20would%20be%20in%20Pakistan's%20interest%20to%20make%20up%20with%20the%20US%20as%20well%20as%20with%20Afghanistan%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bisaria%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704765900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-03%2Fl3479jm_pm-modi-imran-khan-file-650_650x400_22_March_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-delhi-declined-chinas-offer-to-send-deputy-minister-to-india-pak-after-2019-balakot-strikes-4824661%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20aftermath%20of%20India's%20Balakot%20strikes%2C%20several%20countries%20offered%20to%20send%20special%20envoys%20and%20China%20too%20suggested%20that%20it%20could%20send%20its%20deputy%20minister%20to%20both%20countries%20to%20seek%20de-escalation%20but%20New%20Delhi%20declined%20the%20offer%2C%20says%20ex%20diplomat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-delhi-declined-chinas-offer-to-send-deputy-minister-to-india-pak-after-2019-balakot-strikes-4824661%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-delhi-declined-chinas-offer-to-send-deputy-minister-to-india-pak-after-2019-balakot-strikes-4824661%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-delhi-declined-chinas-offer-to-send-deputy-minister-to-india-pak-after-2019-balakot-strikes-4824661%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20last%20time%20an%20airplane's%20door%20broke%20off%20on%20a%20US%20flight%2C%209%20passengers%20were%20sucked%20out%20of%20the%20plane%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222092%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22image%20of%20plane%20on%20ground%20after%20incident%20with%20massive%20hole%20in%20the%20side%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659c9aa21c5c7b8c9a0f0c2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221569%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInvestigators%20inspect%20the%20United%20Airlines%20Flight%20811%20plane%20on%20February%2026%2C%201989.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Sakuma%2FAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20Alaska%20Airlines%20flight%20had%20a%20door%20plug%20blow%20off%20its%20side%20mid-air%20on%20Friday.%20No%20one%20was%20killed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20last%20time%20a%20door%20blew%20off%20mid-flight%20on%20a%20US%20flight%20was%20on%20United%20Airlines%20Flight%20811.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENine%20passengers%20were%20pulled%20out%20of%20the%20plane%20when%20the%20fuselage%20ripped%20apart.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20like%20an%20airline%20passenger's%20worst%20nightmare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20door%20plug%20blew%20off%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-airlines-passenger-thought-plane-would-nosedive-any-second-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlaska%20Airlines%20plane%20mid-flight%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20forcing%20the%20plane%20to%20turn%20around%20and%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-airlines-plane-door-plug-two-most-damaged-seats-empty-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecabin%20was%20damaged%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20no%20one%20was%20seriously%20hurt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20nine%20passengers%20weren't%20so%20lucky%20the%20last%20time%20a%20plane's%20door%20broke%20off%20on%20a%20US%20flight%20over%20three%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20morning%20hours%20of%20February%2024%2C%201989%2C%20Flight%20811%20was%20traveling%20from%20Honolulu%2C%20Hawaii%20to%20Sydney%2C%20Australia%20with%20a%20stop-over%20in%20Auckland%2C%20New%20Zealand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Boeing%20747-122%20was%20still%20ascending%20from%20Honolulu%2C%20it%20was%20suddenly%20rocked%20by%20a%20loud%20sound%20between%2022%2C000%20and%2023%2C000%20feet%20in%20the%20air%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Flessons_learned%2Ftransport_airplane%2Faccidents%2FN4713U%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeconds%20later%2C%20a%20cargo%20door%20toward%20the%20front%20of%20the%20aircraft%20ripped%20off%2C%20taking%20with%20it%20a%20massive%20chunk%20of%20the%20plane's%20fuselage%20and%20leaving%20a%20gaping%20hole%20in%20the%20cabin%20and%20cargo%20area%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENine%20passengers%20in%20that%20section%20of%20the%20plane%20were%20pulled%20out%20into%20the%20night%20sky%2C%20the%20AP%20reported%3B%20at%20least%20one%20of%20them%20was%20sucked%20into%20an%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E''I%20was%20trying%20to%20go%20to%20sleep%20when%20I%20heard%20a%20hissing%20sound%2C''%20passenger%20Gary%20M.%20Garber%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1989%2F02%2F25%2Fus%2F9-lost-23-injured-as-jet-s-skin-rips-over-pacific.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%20''It%20lasted%20about%20three%20or%20four%20seconds%20and%20I%20looked%20at%20my%20wife%20next%20to%20me.%20All%20of%20a%20sudden%20it%20exploded%2C%20and%20I'd%20say%20three%20or%20four%20rows%20of%20people%20on%20the%20right%20side%20of%20the%20plane%20were%20blown%20out.''%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E''There%20were%20about%2018%20inches%20between%20me%20and%20the%20open%20air%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20this%20enormous%20bang%2C%20the%20plane%20whacked%20down%20and%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20passenger%20Suellyn%20Caudwell%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nzherald.co.nz%2Frotorua-daily-post%2Fnews%2Fhorror-of-united-flight-811-suellyn-caudwell-recalls-moment-nine-people-were-sucked-out-of-plane%2F5WWB4K423RQECJAE23MF7Z7W7U%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20Rotorua%20Daily%20Post%20%3C%2Fa%3Edecades%20later%2C%20in%202018.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20see%20the%20moon%20reflected%20in%20the%20water%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20looking%20at%20through%20a%20gaping%20hole%20in%20the%20plane's%20side.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222087%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20inspectors%20look%20at%20the%20severely%20damaged%20United%20Airlines%20Flight%20811%20at%20Honolulu%20Airport%2C%20Feb.%2026%2C%201989.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659ca893ec62ab5daf81c275%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwo%20inspectors%20look%20at%20the%20severely%20damaged%20United%20Airlines%20Flight%20811%20at%20Honolulu%20Airport%2C%20Feb.%2026%2C%201989.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20explosion%20knocked%20down%20the%20flight's%20top%20flight%20attendant%2C%20Laura%20Brentlinger%2C%20who%20grabbed%20onto%20the%20spiral%20metallic%20staircase%20inside%20the%20Boeing%20747-122%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fsacramento%2Fnews%2Fasiana-flight-214-former-flight-attendant-remembers-horror-of-united-flight-811%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECBS%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20hanging%20onto%20the%20rungs%2C%20and%20my%20feet%20were%20literally%20off%20the%20ground%2C%20hanging%20in%20mid-air%2C%26quot%3B%20Brentlinger%20said.%20Brentlinger%20and%20the%20other%20flight%20attendants%20made%20it%20back%20to%20safety%20and%20worked%20quickly%20to%20protect%20the%20other%20passengers%20on%20the%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remember%20screaming%20to%20my%20flying%20partner%2C%20'We're%20supposed%20to%20exude%20confidence%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20CBS%20News.%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20I%20exude%20confidence%20when%20I'm%20scared%20to%20death%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pilots%20managed%20to%20turn%20the%20plane%20around%20and%20make%20an%20emergency%20landing%20back%20at%20Honolulu%20at%20a%20much%20higher%20speed%20than%20normal%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20began%20to%20see%20the%20lights%20of%20Honolulu%20I%20knew%20it%20would%20be%20all%20right%2C%20by%20then%20we%20were%20in%20a%20controlled%20descent%2C%26quot%3B%20Caudwell%20told%20the%20Rotorua%20Daily%20Post.%20%26quot%3BI%20stood%20up%20and%20ran%20as%20fast%20as%20anyone%20could%20run%20and%20when%20I%20looked%20back%20I%20couldn't%20believe%20the%20size%20of%20the%20hole%20in%20the%20plane%20%E2%80%94%20you%20could%20have%20driven%20three%20cars%20through%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20U.S.%20Coast%20Guard%20crewmen%20unload%20an%20interior%20piece%20from%20United%20Airlines%20Flight%20811%20in%20Honolulu%2C%20Hawaii.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659ca8cb1c5c7b8c9a0f0cd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221738%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwo%20U.S.%20Coast%20Guard%20crewmen%20unload%20an%20interior%20piece%20from%20United%20Airlines%20Flight%20811%20in%20Honolulu%2C%20Hawaii.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20federal%20investigators%20probed%20the%20disaster%2C%20the%20parents%20of%20one%20of%20the%20passengers%20wanted%20answers.%20Kevin%20and%20Susan%20Campbell%20launched%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20explosion%2C%20poring%20over%20photos%20and%20thousands%20of%20pages%20of%20technical%20documents%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.seattletimes.com%2Farchive%2F%3Fdate%3D19900227%26slug%3D1058277%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Seattle%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Boeing%20engineer%20later%20said%20in%20a%20hearing%20that%20Boeing%20was%20aware%20of%20flaws%20in%20the%20door's%20locking%20mechanism%20design%20years%20earlier%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Boeing%20warned%20airlines%20to%20reinforce%20their%20doors%20with%20extra%20pieces%20of%20aluminum%2C%20United%20didn't%20find%20any%20flaws%20with%20their%20doors%20and%20didn't%20make%20the%20repairs%20at%20first%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRobert%20Doll%2C%20United's%20vice%20president%20of%20engineering%2C%20said%20at%20the%20hearing%20that%20United%20did%20not%20believe%20the%20locks%20were%20enough%20of%20a%20danger%20to%20justify%20the%20cost%20of%20repairing%20its%20entire%20fleet%20promptly%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Times%20reported.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NTSB%20ultimately%20determined%20that%20faulty%20wiring%20and%20an%20electrical%20short%20caused%20the%20door%20to%20open%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20found%20that%20the%20door's%20mechanism%20design%20had%20a%20flaw%20and%20that%20Boeing%2C%20the%20airlines%2C%20and%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20didn't%20move%20quickly%20enough%20to%20fix%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20several%20opportunities%20for%20the%20manufacturer%2C%20the%20airline%2C%20and%20the%20FAA%2C%20to%20have%20taken%20action%20during%20the%20service%20life%20of%20the%20Boeing%20747%20that%20would%20have%20prevented%20this%20accident%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20NTSB%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-flight-811-history-door-blown-off-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704765829000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659c5dd3ec62ab5daf81ae63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com