%20elaborated%20over%20the%20weekend%20that%20LaPierre%20suffers%20from%20chronic%20Lyme%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20standing%20lockstep%20with%20Mr.%20LaPierre%20for%20more%20than%20three%20years%20litigating%20this%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20side%20wrote%20Sunday%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20NRA%20suddenly%20purports%20to%20reverse%20course.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaPierre's%20departure%20is%20now%20being%20portrayed%20by%20the%20NRA%20as%20an%20example%20of%20%26quot%3Bclear%20corrective%20action%26quot%3B%20and%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20excuse%20to%20avoid%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20her%20filing%2C%20signed%20by%20Monica%20Connell%2C%20a%20special%20counsel%20to%20James.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NRA's%20reference%20to%20misconduct%20by%20%26quot%3Bformer%20rogue%20officers%26quot%3B%20is%20noteworthy%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20as%20a%20designation%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20now%20presumably%20include%5Bs%5D%20Mr.%20LaPierre.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20NRA%20should%20not%20be%20permitted%20to%20present%20Mr.%20LaPierre's%20resignation%20as%20a%20component%20of%20its%20defense%26quot%3B%20at%20trial%2C%20Connell%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20written%20exchange%20between%20the%20NRA%20and%20the%20AG%20came%20ahead%20of%20the%20state's%20opening%20statements%20in%20a%20Manhattan%20courtroom%20Monday%2C%20also%20by%20Connell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20openings%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe%20promised%20jurors%20that%20testimony%20over%20the%20next%20five%20weeks%20would%20show%20that%20loyal%20NRA%20employees%20saw%20LaPierre%20as%20their%20%26quot%3Bking%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20they%20enabled%20him%20to%20squander%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20millions%26quot%3B%20of%20donor%20dollars%20on%20his%20cronies%20and%20his%20own%20lavish%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJurors%20were%20screened%20and%20selected%20in%20secrecy%2C%20behind%20closed%20doors%20in%20the%20judge's%20chambers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJournalists%2C%20including%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20were%20kept%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20the%20process%20despite%20repeatedly%20asking%20the%20judge%20and%20the%20state%20court%20system%20for%20an%20opportunity%20to%20oppose%20in%20advance%20if%20jury%20selection%20was%20being%20held%20in%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20made%20from%20the%20bench%20before%20the%20jurors%20were%20called%20in%2C%20the%20judge%20presiding%20at%20the%20trial%2C%20New%20York%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Joel%20Cohen%2C%20said%20secrecy%20was%20the%20only%20way%20prospective%20jurors%20could%20participate%20%26quot%3Bin%20candor%26quot%3B%20given%20%26quot%3Ba%20number%20of%20sensitive%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20the%20NRA%2C%20LaPierre%2C%20and%20two%20co-defendants%20have%20denied%20wrongdoing%20and%20will%20make%20their%20own%20opening%20statements%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20their%20final%20pretrial%20filing%2C%20the%20gun%20lobby's%20lawyers%20wrote%20that%2C%20especially%20after%20LaPierre's%20recent%20resignation%2C%20the%20AG%20can%20no%20longer%20show%20%26quot%3Bongoing%20or%20imminent%20harm%20to%20the%20public.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20NRA%20has%20stopped%2C%20and%20shows%20no%20intent%20to%20resume%2C%20the%20practices%20of%20which%20the%20NYAG%20complains%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20defense%20wrote%2C%20using%20the%20initials%20for%20%26quot%3BNew%20York%20attorney%20general.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20inference%20is%20underscored%20by%20the%20departure%20of%20Wayne%20LaPierre%2C%20the%20officer%20alleged%20to%20have%20exercised%20'power%20and%20control'%20over%20the%20NRA%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20filing%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJurors%20should%20be%20barred%20from%20holding%20the%20NRA%20liable%20unless%20the%20AG%20proves%20that%20%26quot%3Bimproper%20administration%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20group%20%26quot%3Bis%20continuing%20or%20imminently%20likely%20to%20recur%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20began%20her%20inquiry