0use%20employees%20as%20a%20scapegoat%20for%20bad%20performance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBillionaire%20CEOs%20were%20quick%20to%20sing%20the%20praises%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-rto-billionaire-ceo-threaten-fire-workers-wfh-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20calling%20it%20the%20way%20of%20the%20future%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20they've%20slowly%20changed%20their%20tune.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELate%20last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fshephyken%2F2023%2F09%2F24%2Fnine-out-of-10-companies-will-require-employees-to-return-to-the-office%2F%3Fsh%3D12052a8c2baf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForbes%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%2090%25%20of%20companies%20will%20return%20to%20the%20office%20in%202024%2C%20with%2028%25%20threatening%20to%20fire%20workers%20who%20don't%20comply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20turns%20out%20that%20the%20motivations%20for%20calling%20workers%20back%20to%20the%20office%20may%20have%20less%20to%20do%20with%20employee%20productivity%20or%20profit%20margins%20and%20everything%20to%20do%20with%20catering%20to%20the%20egos%20of%20controlling%20managers%20who%20want%20their%20workers%20back%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4675401%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pittsburgh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Ma%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20business%20administration%20from%20Pitt's%20Katz%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20who%20led%20the%20study%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20started%20the%20research%20hoping%20to%20understand%20why%20some%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20firms%20want%20employees%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%20while%20other%20firms%20avoid%20calling%20them%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalyzing%20firms%20that%20had%20publicly%20announced%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-making-workers-employees-return-to-office-rto-wfh-hybrid-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERTO%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Ma%20examined%20whether%20the%20mandates%20actually%20affected%20financial%20performance%20and%20how%20such%20policies%20impacted%20employee%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20most%20common%20arguments%20management%20suggests%20is%20that%20they%20want%20to%20return%20to%20office%20because%20employee%20productivity%20is%20low%20at%20home%2C%20and%20they%20believe%20returns%20to%20office%20would%20help%20firms%20improve%20performance%20and%20ultimately%20improve%20the%20firm's%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20Ma%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20reason%20they%20give%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20our%20results%20actually%20do%20not%20support%20these%20arguments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENo%20financial%20incentive%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMa%20compared%20each%20firm's%20financial%20performance%20on%20the%20stock%20market%20before%20and%20after%20implementing%20return-to-office%20mandates%20and%20found%20no%20significant%20change%20in%20either%20the%20financial%20performance%20or%20the%20stock%20market%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20potentially%20contributing%20factor%20as%20to%20why%20firm%20performance%20has%20not%20improved%2C%20Ma%20said%2C%20could%20be%20due%20to%20higher%20expenses%20caused%20by%20bringing%20employees%20back%20to%20the%20office.%20Even%20if%20employee%20productivity%20is%20better%20in%20the%20office%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20firm%20also%20needs%20to%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20expenses%20to%20accommodate%20them%20%E2%80%94%20parking%2C%20office%20space%2C%20catering%2C%20or%20other%20in-house%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20which%20he%20says%20mitigates%20the%20positive%20benefits%20of%20enhanced%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2060%25%20of%20company%20leaders%20who%20responded%20to%20a%20recent%20survey%20indicated%20they%20pay%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-from-home-ending-companies-mandate-return-to-office-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2450%20per%20square%20foot%20for%20their%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20on%20average%2C%20if%20we%20take%20a%20look%20at%20all%20these%20benefits%20and%20the%20expense%20average%2C%20the%20net%20benefit%20is%20really%20close%20to%20zero%2C%26quot%3B%20Ma%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20our%20studies%20are%20suggesting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20financial%20benefit%20to%20RTO%20policies%20prompted%20Ma's%20team%20to%20look%20into%20other%20possible%20explanations%20for%20why%20managers%20call%20their%20employees%20back%20to%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERTO%20is%20favored%20by%20controlling%20bosses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20theme%20among%20news%20articles%20about%20RTO%20policies%20that%20Ma's%20team%20reviewed%20highlighted%20workplace%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-mandates-employees-managers-fight-messy-remote-work-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtrol%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20indicating%20managers%20are%20trying%20to%20use%20the%20return%20to%20office%20mandates%20to%20reassert%20their%20control%20over%20the%20employees%20even%20if%20it%20costs%20the%20firm%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20research%2C%20Ma%20calls%20this%20%26quot%3Bthe%20agency%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20the%20managers%20do%20not%20make%20decisions%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20shareholder%20or%20the%20firm%20but%20based%20on%20their%20own%20best%20interest.%20By%20regaining%20control%20of%20the%20employees%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20managers%20feel%20a%20false%20sense%20of%20control%2C%20which%20makes%20them%20feel%20more%20secure%20about%20their%20job%20and%20their%20own%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20putting%20the%20%26quot%3Bcontrolling%20manager%26quot%3B%20theory%20to%20the%20test%2C%20Ma%20expected%20to%20find%20more%20return-to-office%20mandates%20implemented%20by%20higher-profile%20managers%20in%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20indeed%20what%20we%20found%2C%26quot%3B%20Ma%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20found%20RTO%20mandates%20are%20more%20common%20among%20male%20CEOs%20and%20more%20powerful%20CEOs.%20So%20that's%20consistent%20with%20these%20managers%20using%20RTO%20mandates%20to%20reassert%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20my%20personal%20belief%20that%2C%20as%20prior%20research%20suggests%2C%20most%20CEOs%20are%20very%20narcissistic.%20That%20means%20they%20are%20used%20to%20being%20in%20the%20center%20of%20everything%20and%20issuing%20orders%20for%20employees%20to%20follow.%20But%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20they%20feel%20kind%20of%20like%20they're%20losing%20power%20because%20employees%20became%20more%20and%20more%20aware%20of%20their%20rights%20during%20the%20great%20resignation.%20So%2C%20the%20managers%20feel%20that%20they%20are%20losing%20their%20power%20inside%20the%20firm%2C%20basically%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20they%20want%20to%20grab%20their%20power%20back%20in%20this%20relationship.%20And%20that's%20the%20reason%20we%20found%20such%20results.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrevious%20studies%20have%20found%20that%20CEOs%20with%20narcissistic%20traits%20made%20an%20average%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudy-says-narcissistic-ceos-get-paid-more-2014-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24512%20million%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20peers%20who%20spent%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20time%20at%20their%20companies.%20Still%2C%20companies%20with%20extremely%20self-absorbed%20bosses%20also%20tend%20to%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnarcissistic-ceos-and-accounting-paper-2015-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshadier%20accounting%20practices%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EManagers%20could%20be%20using%20employee%20performance%20as%20a%20scapegoat%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20firms%20performed%20exceptionally%20well%20financially%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20while%20others%20floundered.%20Ma's%20research%20suggests%20RTO%20policies%20may%20offer%20managers%20a%20possible%20scapegoat%20to%20explain%20away%20poor%20performance%20by%20blaming%20it%20on%20employees%20who%20underperformed%20while%20working%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20rather%20than%20say%20the%20poor%20performance%20is%20because%20of%20the%20manager's%20bad%20decisions%2C%20they%20will%20try%20to%20tell%20investors%2C%20'It's%20not%20my%20fault%2C%20it's%20the%20employees%20who%20are%20being%20lazy%20at%20home%2C'%26quot%3B%20Ma%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20scapegoat%20explanation%20were%20true%2C%20Ma%20hypothesized%20he'd%20find%20more%20RTO%20mandates%20among%20firms%20whose%20performance%20was%20bad%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20exactly%20what%20we%20found.%20We%20found%20that%20return-to-office%20mandates%20are%20more%20common%20among%20firms%20with%20poor%20stock%20performance%20and%20stock%20returns%2C%26quot%3B%20Ma%20said.%20%26quot%3BLike%2C%20really%20bad%20stock%20returns%20during%20the%20pandemic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIn-office%20mandates%20hurt%20employee%20satisfaction%20and%20retention%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20analyze%20the%20impact%20of%20strict%20RTO%20policies%20on%20workers%2C%20Ma's%20team%20collected%20all%20the%20employee%20reviews%20on%20Glassdoor%20for%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20found%20that%20after%20return%20to%20office%20mandates%2C%20employees'%20job%20satisfaction%20significantly%20drops%2C%26quot%3B%20Ma%20said.%20%26quot%3BBased%20on%20our%20findings%2C%20there's%20a%20significant%20drop%20in%20job%20satisfaction%2C%20and%20that%20decrease%20translates%20into%20lower%20productivity%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0even%20though%20maybe%20before%20the%20pandemic%20it%20was%20true%20that%20people%20were%20more%20productive%20in%20the%20office.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrithwiraj%20Choudhury%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20and%20remote%20work%20expert%2C%20found%20in%20recent%20research%20that%20employees%20who%20worked%20from%20home%2075%25%20of%20the%20time%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-working-model-wfh-work-from-home-policy-office-trends-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20most%20productive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20allow%20flexibility%2C%20it%20expands%20your%20talent%20pool%2C%26quot%3B%20Choudhury%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BWhether%20the%20economy%20is%20contracting%20or%20expanding%2C%20the%20best%20workers%20always%20have%20outside%20options.%20And%20so%20I%20think%20if%20you%20as%20a%20company%20have%20a%20model%20that%20doesn't%20give%20the%20best%20employees%20flexibility%20some%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20not%20every%20one%20of%20them%2C%20but%20some%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20will%20be%20poached%20by%20competitors.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicholas%20Bloom%2C%20a%20Stanford%20economics%20professor%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fneed-to-hire-workers-in-a-hot-job-market-let-them-do-some-remote-work-506f72e6%3Fmod%3Dhp_lead_pos8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20workers%20increasingly%20value%20a%20flexible%20workplace%20and%20view%20hybrid%20work%20accommodations%20as%20equal%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-work-from-home-benefits-as-good-as-raise-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E8%25%20pay%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Journal%20also%20reported%20that%20employers%20that%20insist%20upon%20bringing%20employees%20back%20to%20in-person%20work%20are%20seeing%20slower%20hiring%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20with%20companies%20that%20have%20full-time%20remote%20work%20seeing%20a%205%25%20increase%20in%20their%20staffing%20levels%20over%20the%20last%20year%2C%20compared%20to%20just%202.6%25%20for%20full-time%20in-person%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20forcing%20everyone%20back%20to%20in-office%20work%2C%20Ma%20says%20high-performing%20employees%20who%20perform%20well%20at%20home%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20continue%20at%20home.%20This%20would%20benefit%20the%20employee%20as%20well%20as%20the%20firm%20in%20the%20long-term%2C%20he%20said%2C%20because%20it%20would%20help%20the%20firm%20to%20better%20retain%20its%20high-performing%20employees%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0especially%20because%20high-performing%20employees%20could%20easily%20find%20other%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20software%20developer%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company's%20strict%20RTO%20mandate%20resulted%20in%20his%20resignation%20from%20the%20company%2C%20seeking%20a%20new%20remote-first%20role%20and%20leaving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-rto-cross-country-move-worker-quit-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24200%2C000%20of%20unvested%20stocks%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20table%20rather%20than%20return%20to%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20administrator%20in%20Arizona%20also%20left%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-return-to-office-quit-job-micromanager-boss-salary-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix-figure%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20its%20return-to-office%20policy%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20firms%20could%20call%20back%20the%20employees%20who%20are%20not%20performing%20as%20well%20as%20expected%2C%26quot%3B%20Ma%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20should%20not%20call%20back%20most%20employees%20who%20are%20performing%20well%20back%20to%20the%20office.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Ma%20advocates%20for%20monthly%20team-building%20activities%20in%20person%20to%20maintain%20company%20culture%2C%20which%20can%20be%20essential%20for%20problem-solving%20and%20brainstorming%20new%20ideas.%20Still%2C%20he%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bworking%20in%20the%20office%20every%20day%20may%20not%20necessarily%20create%20a%20better%20team%2C%20and%20also%20sometimes%20it%20could%20create%20conflicts%20between%20team%20members.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20firms%20need%20to%20treat%20the%20employee%20more%20humanely%20and%20also%20give%20them%20more%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20Ma%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20see%20no%20reason%20for%20these%20big%20firms%20to%20treat%20their%20employees%20more%20harshly%20because%20they're%20working%20from%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-policies-dont-improve-employee-performance-company-value-controlling-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704759517000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659b50c9ec62ab5daf816261%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-policies-dont-improve-employee-performance-company-value-controlling-bosses-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20studying%20RTO%20policies%20of%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20companies%20found%20no%20improvement%20in%20the%20value%20of%20the%20businesses%20that%20brought%20workers%20back%20to%20the%20office.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktangalakislippert%40businessinsider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A38%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-policies-dont-improve-employee-performance-company-value-controlling-bosses-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%