onship%20%E2%80%94%20but%20sometimes%20they're%20unavoidable.%20Here's%20how%20to%20move%20past%20them.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221630%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20in%20shop%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659810b9ec62ab5daf80f5f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221222%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThere%20are%20three%20main%20reasons%20partners%20might%20keep%20secrets%20from%20each%20other%2C%20according%20to%20therapist%20Amy%20Morin.%3Cp%3EJohner%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20a%20fine%20line%20between%20privacy%20and%20secrecy%20in%20relationships.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESecret-keeping%20often%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20an%20unhealthy%20relationship%2C%20therapist%20Amy%20Morin%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20explained%20how%20partners%20can%20stop%20the%20behavior%20and%20move%20on%20from%20past%20secrets.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20healthy%20relationship%2C%20it's%20normal%20to%20keep%20aspects%20of%20your%20life%20private%2C%20like%20your%20social-media%20passwords%20and%20conversations%20you%20have%20with%20your%20own%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20find%20yourself%20keeping%20secrets%20from%20your%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20withholding%20information%20or%20lying%20about%20something%20because%20it%20could%20hurt%20or%20upset%20them%20%E2%80%94%20the%20consequences%20of%20getting%20caught%20could%20be%20greater%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-let-go-of-secrets-causing-you-shame2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esharing%20the%20secret%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20therapist%20Amy%20Morin%20wrote%20in%20her%20book%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrong-couples-dont-do-bad-habits-avoid-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3B13%20Things%20Mentally%20Strong%20Couples%20Don't%20Do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20it%2C%20Morin%20dedicates%20an%20entire%20chapter%20to%20secret-keeping%2C%20including%20why%20people%20do%20it%2C%20and%20how%20to%20change%20course%20to%20improve%20your%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20does%20secret-keeping%20say%20about%20your%20relationship%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMorin%20wrote%20that%20secret-keeping%20is%20often%20a%20sign%20of%20an%20unhealthy%20relationship%20because%20it%20suggests%20partners%20don't%20trust%20each%20other%2C%20or%20worry%20their%20partner%20won't%20care%20enough%20to%20work%20through%20whatever%20it%20is%20they%20are%20hiding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20in%20a%20rocky%20relationship%20already%2C%20you%20may%20be%20harboring%20secrets%20because%20you%20know%20your%20partner%20won't%20be%20supportive%20or%20it%20will%20just%20lead%20to%20more%20arguments%2C%26quot%3B%20Morin%20wrote%20in%20her%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20secrets%2C%20which%20always%20sow%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsigns-someone-doesnt-trust-you-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edistrust%20in%20a%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20different%20from%20privacy%2C%20or%20keeping%20benign%20information%20private%20from%20your%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivacy%20is%20normal%20in%20relationships%20because%20it%20shows%20that%20each%20partner%20has%20their%20own%20autonomy%2C%20and%20respects%20and%20trusts%20their%20partner%20to%20have%20a%20sense%20of%20independence%20too%2C%20Morin%20wrote.%20For%20example%2C%20it's%20normal%20to%20keep%20private%20a%20conversation%20where%20a%20friend%20confided%20in%20you%20about%20something%20unrelated%20to%20your%20partner.%20Having%20sole%20access%20to%20your%20emails%20and%20enjoying%20your%20free%20time%20without%20constantly%20alerting%20your%20partner%20of%20your%20whereabouts%20are%20other%20forms%20of%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20avoid%20telling%20your%20partner%20information%20that%20could%20hurt%20them%20or%20make%20them%20upset%20or%20disappointed%20with%20you%20%E2%80%94%20like%20not%20sharing%20that%20your%20ex%20recently%20reached%20out%20to%20you%2C%20asking%20to%20meet%20for%20coffee%2C%20or%20spending%20over%20your%20agreed-upon%20budget%20%E2%80%94%20that%20could%20constitute%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftherapist-in-open-relationship-emotional-cheating-is-secrecy-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecrecy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Morin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20do%20people%20keep%20secrets%20from%20their%20partners%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20main%20reasons%20why%20people%20keep%20secrets%20from%20others%20they%20care%20about%2C%20including%20in%20romantic%20relationships%2C%20according%20to%20Morin.%20They%20are%20to%20protect%20themselves%2C%20their%20partner%2C%20or%20their%20relationship%2C%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20working%20with%20couples%2C%20she's%20often%20found%20that%20one%20partner%20feels%20driven%20to%20keep%20a%20sensitive%20matter%20to%20themself%20because%20they%20know%20their%20partner%20will%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fred-flags-in-a-relationship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebig%2C%20negative%20reaction%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20don't%20want%20to%20ruin%20the%20relationship%2C%20cause%20their%20partner%20pain%2C%20or%20have%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20their%20wrongdoing%2C%20so%20they%20stay%20quiet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20reason%2C%20keeping%20secrets%20can%20have%20the%20same%20corrosive%20effect%20on%20a%20couple's%20bond.%20Understanding%20exactly%20why%20you're%20harboring%20a%20secret%20can%20help%20you%20come%20clean%20and%20move%20forward%2C%20Morin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20move%20past%20secret-keeping%20in%20a%20relationship%20in%20three%20steps%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20book%2C%20Morin%20shared%20tips%20for%20remedying%20past%20instances%20of%20secret-keeping%20between%20partners%2C%20and%20for%20avoiding%20the%20same%20pattern%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20partner%20whose%20secret%20was%20found%20out%20should%20reflect%20on%20why%20they%20kept%20it%2C%20and%20take%20responsibility%20for%20their%20behavior%2C%20according%20to%20Morin.%20The%20partner%20who%20learned%20of%20the%20secret%20should%20consider%20what%20they%20need%20to%20move%20forward%20and%20regain%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20couples%20should%20have%20a%20conversation%20about%20what%20they%20want%20privacy%20to%20look%20like%20in%20their%20relationships%20moving%20forward.%20Unlike%20secrecy%2C%20privacy%20means%20keeping%20certain%20details%2C%20ones%20that%20would%20neither%20benefit%20nor%20hurt%20your%20partner%2C%20to%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Morin%2C%20most%20couples%20never%20talk%20about%20these%20fine%20lines%2C%20leading%20to%20major%20arguments%20when%20a%20situation%20that%20teeters%20between%20privacy%20and%20secrecy%20arises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiscussing%20how%20you%20and%20your%20partner%20want%20to%20handle%20things%20%E2%80%94%20like%20social-media%20passwords%2C%20personal%20conversations%20with%20your%20loved%20ones%20that%20don't%20involve%20them%2C%20and%20reaching%20out%20to%20ex-partners%20%E2%80%94%20can%20prevent%20assumptions%20and%20mistrust%20going%20forward%2C%20wrote%20Morin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20avoid%20secret-keeping%20in%20the%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20secret-keeping%20in%20your%20dynamic%2C%20practice%20being%20more%20aware%20of%20your%20reactions%20during%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhard-conversations-about-dating-to-normalize-how-to-have-them-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifficult%20conversations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20work%20to%20change%20them%2C%20Morin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20partner%20shares%20something%20hard%2C%20they%20should%20admit%20it%20was%20difficult%20to%20put%20it%20out%20there.%20Then%2C%20the%20other%20partner%20should%20do%20their%20best%20to%20hear%20them%20out%20without%20yelling%2C%20belittling%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsigns-you-might-be-over-critical-and-controlling-in-relationship-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecoming%20defensive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Morin%20wrote.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EInstead%2C%20say%20%26quot%3BThank%20you%20for%20being%20honest%20with%20me.%20I%20know%20that%20must%20have%20been%20hard%20to%20share.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you're%20thinking%20%26quot%3BHow%20could%20you%3F!%26quot%3B%20in%20your%20head%2C%20tempering%20your%20initial%20reaction%20shows%20your%20partner%20that%20you%20want%20to%20understand%20them%20and%20work%20together%2C%20even%20when%20it's%20hard%2C%20according%20to%20Morin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20you%20can%20ask%20for%20time%20alone%20to%20process%20what%20they%20just%20told%20you%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20feeling%20upset.%20Then%2C%20calmly%20discuss%20it%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecrets-destroy-trust-relationship-therapist-advice-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704757801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6598165e6979d7371820b796%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecrets-destroy-trust-relationship-therapist-advice-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Finding%20out%20your%20partner%20was%20keeping%20a%20secret%20could%20destroy%20trust%20in%20your%20relationship.%20A%20therapist%20shares%20advice%20on%20how%20to%20fix%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnaftulin%40businessinsider.com%20(Julia%20Naftulin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecrets-destroy-trust-relationship-therapist-advice-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AppleCare%3A%20What%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20coverage%2C%20benefits%2C%20and%20value%20of%20your%20Apple%20devices%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222168%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20children%20hold%20iPhones%20at%20an%20Apple%20store%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659c2a061c5c7b8c9a0eda5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELi%20Hongbo%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20devices%20and%20our%20increasing%20reliance%20on%20them%20for%20day-to-day%20life%2C%20you%20may%20have%20thought%20about%20whether%20or%20not%20to%20purchase%20AppleCare%2B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20opt%20to%20purchase%20AppleCare%2B%20at%20checkout%2C%20you%20have%20up%20to%2060%20days%20from%20the%20purchase%20date%20to%20reconsider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what's%20covered%2C%20how%20to%20check%20what%20coverage%20you%20currently%20have%2C%20and%20the%20options%20available%20for%20purchase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20covered%20under%20AppleCare%2B%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAppleCare%2B%20is%20an%20extended%20warranty%20program%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-mac-products-great-classic-boring-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20iPhones%2C%20Apple%20Watches%2C%20AirPods%2C%20Mac%2C%20and%20iPads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20AppleCare%2B%20plan%20can%20only%20be%20purchased%20within%2060%20days%20of%20the%20original%20purchase%20date%20of%20your%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAppleCare%2B%20extends%20the%20standard%20warranty%20to%20two%20years%20and%20covers%20up%20to%20two%20accidental%20damage%20incidents%20(like%20dropping%20your%20phone%20and%20breaking%20the%20screen)%20every%2012%20months.%20Each%20incident%20is%20subject%20to%20a%20service%20fee%20(%2429%20for%20screen%20damage%2C%20%2499%20for%20any%20other%20type%20of%20accidental%20damage)%2C%20plus%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20iPhone's%20battery%20can%20be%20serviced%20if%20it%20retains%20less%20than%2080%20percent%20of%20its%20original%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20also%20get%2024%2F7%20priority%20access%20to%20Apple%20experts%20via%20chat%20or%20phone%20to%20help%20troubleshoot%20any%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20it%20does%20not%20cover%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20lose%20your%20iPhone%20or%20if%20it's%20stolen%2C%20unless%20you%20purchase%20AppleCare%2B%20with%20Theft%20and%20Loss%20(%24149%20fee%20per%20incident%20of%20theft%20or%20loss).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3EIs%20AppleCare%2B%20worth%20it%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAppleCare%2B%20can%20pay%20for%20itself%20if%20you%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20drop%20your%20device%20and%20crack%20its%20screen.%20Screen%20and%20back%20glass%20repairs%20can%20cost%20hundreds%2C%20but%20AppleCare%2B%20substantially%20lowers%20that%20fee%20to%20only%20a%20%2429%20deductible%20per%20incident%2C%20including%20unlimited%20incident%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAppleCare%2B%20also%20provides%2024%2F7%20access%20to%20Apple%20experts%20and%20covers%20battery%20replacement%20if%20the%20battery%20retains%20less%20than%2080%25%20of%20its%20original%20capacity.%20Access%20to%2024%2F7%20support%20by%20phone%20or%20online%20from%20Apple%20experts%20can%20be%20crucial%20in%20helping%20to%20diagnose%20an%20issue%20you're%20experiencing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20another%20tier%20of%20AppleCare%2B%20called%20%26quot%3BAppleCare%2B%20Theft%20and%20Loss%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20it%20is%20only%20available%20for%20purchase%20in%20the%20US%2C%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20Australia%2C%20France%2C%20Italy%2C%20and%20Spain.%20For%20up%20to%20two%20incidents%20of%20theft%20in%20a%20calendar%20year%2C%20AppleCare%2B%20Theft%20and%20Loss%20will%20include%20device%20replacement%20with%20a%20%24149%20deductible%20per%20incident%2C%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20cost%20of%20replacing%20your%20device%20outright.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20much%20does%20AppleCare%2B%20cost%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20AppleCare%2B%20varies%20depending%20on%20the%20device%20you%20want%20to%20cover%20and%20how%20you%20want%20to%20pay.%20For%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-iphone%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPhone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20can%20choose%20two%20years%20of%20coverage%20or%20a%20monthly%20subscription%20service%20that%20lasts%20as%20long%20as%20you%20have%20the%20device%20and%20keep%20paying.%20The%20cost%20varies%20from%20%2479%20to%20%24199%20for%20two%20years%20of%20iPhone%20coverage%20(or%20between%20%243.99%2Fmonth%20and%20%249.99%2Fmonth%20for%20monthly%20coverage).%20Including%20AppleCare%2B%20with%20Theft%20and%20Loss%20increases%20the%20cost%20to%20between%20%24149%20and%20%24269%20for%20two%20years%20of%20coverage%20or%20%247.49%2Fmonth%20to%20%2413.49%2Fmonth%20for%20monthly%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-apple-ipads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPad%3C%2Fa%3E%20you%20can%20purchase%20either%20month-to-month%20coverage%20for%20between%20%243.49%20and%20%247.99%20or%20two%20years%20of%20coverage%20for%20between%20%2469%20and%20%24149%2C%20depending%20on%20your%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20Watches%20do%20not%20have%20all%20options%20available%20for%20every%20model.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Apple%20Watch%20H%C3%A8rmes%20only%20has%20a%20monthly%20(%244.99%2Fmonth)%20and%20three-year%20(%24149)%20option.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-apple-watch%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20Watch%3C%2Fa%3E%20lineup%20only%20ha