-history-photos-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprevious%20generation%20of%20737%20aircraft%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20came%20before%20the%20Max%20family%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Next%20Generation%2C%20or%20NG%20for%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NG%20planes%20came%20in%20four%20variants%20from%20smallest%20to%20largest%3A%20%E2%88%92600%2C-700%2C-800%2C%20and%20-900.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELearning%20on%20the%20fly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20already%20at%20the%20airport%20or%20on%20the%20plane%20and%20something%20spooks%20you%2C%20and%20you%20want%20to%20check%20which%20kind%20of%20plane%20you're%20on%2C%20you%20have%20a%20few%20options%20to%20see%20if%20it's%20a%20Max%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirlines%20sometimes%20put%20the%20aircraft's%20brand%20and%20model%20on%20the%20jet's%20exterior%2C%20either%20at%20the%20front%20of%20the%20plane%20under%20the%20cockpit%20or%20toward%20the%20back%20under%20the%20last%20few%20windows.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it's%20not%20there%2C%20every%20plane%20has%20a%20very%20prominent%20registration%20number%20on%20its%20exterior.%20You%20can%20search%20this%20online%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fregistry.faa.gov%2Faircraftinquiry%2Fsearch%2Fnnumberinquiry%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFAA's%20database%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20find%20the%20exact%20model%20associated%20with%20the%20tail%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20the%20seatback%20pocket%20safety%20card%20will%20also%20tell%20you%20what%20type%20of%20plane%20you're%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20tried%20everything%20you%20can%20think%20of%20and%20are%20still%20unsure%2C%20any%20airline%20employee%20should%20be%20able%20to%20tell%20you%20what%20plane%20model%20it%20is.%20All%20you%20have%20to%20do%20is%20ask!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-tell-you-are-flying-boeing-737-max-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A17047558010